{
  "texts": [
    "Suk and Shen [105] suggest a hybrid model for identifying AD built on CNN and Sparse Regression Networks.",
    "Multiple Sparse Regression Networks were employed by the model to produce different targeted images.",
    "Next, CNN merged these target-level descriptions best determined the output label.",
    "The 16-layered VGGNet was altered by Billones et al. [10] for dividing the patients into three categories according to structural MRI: AD, MCI, and HC scanning.",
    "Testing carried out for the study showed that the researchers were successfully carrying out categories accurately."
  ]
}